        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The Biden administration is introducing newer rules that further limit <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-14-01-2025-h2-2-nvidia-ai-chip-sales" target="_blank">Nvidia AI chip sales</a>. The rules aim to curb China and Russia's AI advancements. Businesses in restricted nations must comply with U.S. security and human rights standards to purchase chips. The restrictions aim to secure AI dominance but face criticism from Nvidia and lawmakers over potential market disruptions. Supply chain activities and gaming chips were excluded from the new curbs.  Shares of Nvidia fell 2% to $133.23, while AMD and Intel shares fell on the news.</p>
