          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Change Global Investment LLC plans to double its <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-14-01-2025-wn1-3-exposure-to-brazilian-equities" target="_blank">exposure to Brazilian equities</a>. The managing director, Thea Jamison, sees Brazil’s discounted valuations as attractive. The Ibovespa index trades at historically low multiples while dividend yields climb. Jamison is bullish on exporters and domestic cash-and-carry firms. The firm’s reallocation highlights a broader shift among investors reducing China's exposure amid geopolitical tensions and turning to Brazil’s potential for growth and shareholder returns.</p>
