          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Yinson Holdings is close to raising $1 billion from major investors for its FPSO unit. Investors include Abu Dhabi Investment Authority and British Columbia Investment Management Corp. The financing supports Yinson’s growth in offshore oil and gas projects. With contracts involving Petrobras and BP, Yinson’s strategic moves could position it as a <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-14-01-2025-wn2-4-leader-in-the-FPSO-market" target="_blank">leader in the FPSO market</a>, addressing rising global energy demands.</p>
