          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Macroeconomic factors weighed on UK markets last week. Concerns over inflation and fiscal deficits prompted sterling to hit its <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-14-01-2025-wn3-5-lowest-point-since-2023" target="_blank">lowest point since 2023</a>. The traders are currently awaiting inflation data, which could reaffirm high consumer price growth. The UK government remains pressured to stabilize its financial markets and restore investor confidence.</p>
